<BaseLayout title="Post Office FD Rates 2026 - Government-Backed Fixed Deposits | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span><a href="/pages/investments">Investments</a><span>/</span><span>Post Office FD Rates</span></div>
      <h1>Post Office <span class="gradient-text">FD Interest Rates</span> 2026</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Government-backed Post Office Fixed Deposits offer competitive rates with sovereign guarantee. Enjoy tax-saving benefits on 5-year tenure and complete safety of your capital with India Post's trusted Time Deposit scheme.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item"><i class="fas fa-shield-halved"></i><span>Government Backed</span></div>
        <div class="highlight-item"><i class="fas fa-percent"></i><span>6.90% – 7.50%</span></div>
        <div class="highlight-item"><i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i><span>Min ₹1,000</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>Post Office Time Deposit (FD) Scheme</h2></div>
            <p>Post Office Fixed Deposits, officially known as Post Office Time Deposits (POTD), are small savings schemes offered by India Post under the aegis of the Ministry of Finance. These deposits carry sovereign guarantee from the Government of India, making them one of the safest investment options available — even safer than bank FDs where insurance is limited to ₹5 lakh.</p>
            <p>Post Office FDs are available in tenures of 1, 2, 3, and 5 years. The interest rates are reviewed quarterly by the government and are often competitive with or higher than major bank FD rates. The 5-year Post Office FD qualifies for tax deduction under Section 80C, making it a popular choice among tax-saving investors.</p>
            <p>With over 1.55 lakh post office branches across India, accessibility is a major advantage. The minimum deposit is just ₹1,000 with no maximum limit. You can also open a joint account with up to 3 adults. Interest is compounded quarterly but paid annually.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Current Rates</span><h2>Post Office FD Rates (Q1 April–June 2026)</h2></div>
            <table class="rate-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Tenure</th><th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th><th>Compounding</th><th>Tax Saving (80C)</th><th>Maturity Value (₹1 Lakh)</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>1 Year</strong></td><td>6.90%</td><td>Quarterly</td><td>No</td><td>₹1,07,081</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>2 Years</strong></td><td>7.00%</td><td>Quarterly</td><td>No</td><td>₹1,14,888</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>3 Years</strong></td><td>7.10%</td><td>Quarterly</td><td>No</td><td>₹1,23,489</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>5 Years</strong></td><td>7.50%</td><td>Quarterly</td><td>Yes (u/s 80C)</td><td>₹1,44,995</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><em>*Rates as announced by the Ministry of Finance for Q1 FY 2026-27. Rates are subject to quarterly revision. Maturity values are approximate based on quarterly compounding.</em></p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Benefits of Post Office FD</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Sovereign Guarantee</strong><p>Post Office FDs are backed by the Government of India with no upper limit on guarantee. Unlike bank FDs where DICGC covers only ₹5 lakh, your entire deposit in a Post Office FD is government-guaranteed.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Section 80C Tax Benefit</strong><p>The 5-year Post Office FD qualifies for tax deduction up to ₹1.5 lakh under Section 80C. This makes it a risk-free tax-saving option comparable to PPF but with a shorter lock-in period.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Competitive Interest Rates</strong><p>Post Office FD rates are often higher than those of major PSU banks, especially for the 5-year tenure at 7.50%. The government reviews rates quarterly, ensuring they remain competitive with market conditions.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Wide Accessibility</strong><p>With over 1.55 lakh branches, Post Offices are present in every town and village across India. You can also access your account through India Post's internet banking and mobile banking services.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Low Minimum Deposit</strong><p>Start with just ₹1,000 and invest in multiples of ₹100. There is no maximum limit on the deposit amount, making it accessible for everyone from small savers to high-net-worth individuals.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Loan and Premature Withdrawal</strong><p>Premature withdrawal is allowed after 6 months (with reduced interest). Loan facility is available after 6 months of account opening for 1-year, 2-year, and 3-year deposits at an interest rate of FD rate + 2%.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">How to Open</span><h2>How to Open a Post Office FD</h2></div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Visit Nearest Post Office</h3><p>Go to any Head Post Office or Sub Post Office. You can also open an FD online through the India Post Internet Banking portal (DOP eBanking) if you have an existing savings account.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Submit KYC Documents</h3><p>Provide Aadhaar card, PAN card (mandatory for deposits above ₹50,000), and 2 passport-size photographs. Fill the Time Deposit account opening form available at the counter.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Choose Tenure & Deposit</h3><p>Select from 1, 2, 3, or 5-year tenure. For tax saving, choose the 5-year option. Deposit cash, cheque, or transfer from your Post Office savings account. Minimum ₹1,000.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Receive Certificate & Earn</h3><p>Get your Time Deposit certificate or passbook entry as proof. Interest is compounded quarterly and credited annually. On maturity, principal plus interest is credited to your linked savings account.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

