  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">FAQs</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Post Office FD</h2></div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Is Post Office FD safer than Bank FD?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Yes, in terms of guarantee coverage. Post Office FDs carry sovereign guarantee from the Government of India with no upper limit — your entire deposit is fully protected. Bank FDs are insured by DICGC only up to ₹5 lakh per depositor per bank. For deposits exceeding ₹5 lakh, Post Office FDs offer superior safety.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Do senior citizens get extra interest on Post Office FD?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>No, unlike bank FDs, Post Office FDs do not offer any additional interest for senior citizens. The rates are the same for all depositors regardless of age. However, senior citizens can benefit from the Senior Citizens Savings Scheme (SCSS) at post offices, which offers 8.20% per annum with quarterly interest payout.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Can I open a Post Office FD online?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Yes, if you have a Post Office savings account linked to Internet Banking (DOP eBanking), you can open a Time Deposit online. You can also use the India Post Mobile Banking app. For first-time users, the initial savings account must be opened at a branch, after which online FD creation is available.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Is TDS deducted on Post Office FD interest?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Yes, TDS at 10% is deducted on Post Office FD interest if the annual interest exceeds ₹40,000 (₹50,000 for senior citizens) across all Post Office deposits. You can submit Form 15G/15H to avoid TDS if your total income is below the taxable limit. PAN is mandatory for deposits above ₹50,000.</p></div></div></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-question"><span>Can I transfer my Post Office FD to another post office?</span><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></div><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner"><p>Yes, Post Office FDs can be transferred from one post office to another across India without any charges. Simply submit a transfer request at your current post office branch. With CBS (Core Banking Solution) implementation, many post offices now support instant transfer. You can also link your FD to any CBS-enabled post office.</p></div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

